From c9e1e47a6039432f02037ad6da50ab6215b95e1f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: John Garry <john.g.garry@oracle.com>
Date: Wed, 15 Apr 2026 15:53:58 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] nvme-multipath: put module reference when delayed removal
 work is canceled
Git-commit: 3f150f0f010f234f34a67897344f18e68fe803f7
Patch-mainline: v7.1-rc2
References: bsc#1268465

The delayed disk removal work is canceled when a NS (re)appears. However,
we do not put the module reference grabbed in nvme_mpath_remove_disk(), so
fix that.

Reviewed-by: Christoph Hellwig <hch@lst.de>
Reviewed-by: Nilay Shroff <nilay@linux.ibm.com>
Reviewed-by: Chaitanya Kulkarni <kch@nvidia.com>
Signed-off-by: John Garry <john.g.garry@oracle.com>
Signed-off-by: Keith Busch <kbusch@kernel.org>
Signed-off-by: Ales Novak <alnovak@suse.com>
---
 drivers/nvme/host/core.c | 3 ++-
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/nvme/host/core.c b/drivers/nvme/host/core.c
index ca474a12d35a0..3e41b93ca38a3 100644
--- a/drivers/nvme/host/core.c
+++ b/drivers/nvme/host/core.c
@@ -4058,7 +4058,8 @@ static int nvme_init_ns_head(struct nvme_ns *ns, struct nvme_ns_info *info)
 	mutex_unlock(&ctrl->subsys->lock);
 
 #ifdef CONFIG_NVME_MULTIPATH
-	cancel_delayed_work(&head->remove_work);
+	if (cancel_delayed_work(&head->remove_work))
+		module_put(THIS_MODULE);
 #endif
 	return 0;
 
-- 
2.54.0

